Defendant in custody.    
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing, his probation having been revoked effective 04-17-18.   
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of two (2) years.    One (1) year initial confinement, followed by one (1) year extended supervision concurrent with 15 CF 202.   Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.    Conditions of extended supervision are: 
1) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
2) AODA assessment and follow through counseling; 
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
5) Pay costs of action; 
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.   
Defendant is entitled to 621 days sentence credit.   
Minutes.

NO CONTEST plea entered to the charge of possesas THC with intent to deliver.  Convicted.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) spend eight (8) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing 09-29-15 by 8:00 a.m.;
3) additional four (4) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agent's discretion and upon order of the court;
4) maintain fulltime employment/schooling/combination;
5) acquire a diploma or HSED;
6) AODA assessment;
7) submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
8) complete two hundred fifty (250) hour of community service within the first 2 years of probation;
9) pay court costs of $518.00.  $500.00 cash bail applied;
10) Submit to DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
11) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
The Court orders expungement under Section 973.015 upon successful completion of the sentence.
